mutually agree to a demilitarization of the safe areas and their immediate surroundings and the benefits this would bring to all parties in terms of the cessation of attacks on the safe areas and of launching military attacks therefrom;
4.1.1_res_intro: CZR FRN GMY HON NTH OMA UKG

1.5_substance: cooperate fully with UNPROFOR in the fulfillment of its immigration and customs control functions deriving from S/RES/769
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: withdraw elements of national military forces or make them subject to the authority of the government of Bosnia and Herzegovina or disband and disarm them with their weapons placed under effective international monitoring
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN UKG

1.5_substance: refrain from any action intended to destroy alter conceal or damage any evidence of violations of international humanitarian law and preserve such evidence
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZE FRN GMY ITA RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: demands that all detention camps throughout the territory of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina be closed
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZE FRN GMY ITA RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: conclude immediately with the government of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina a cease-fire agreement under the auspices of UNPROFOR in Gorazde and throughout the territory of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina leading to an agreement on cessation of hostilities
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG

1.5_substance: continue efforts in the framework of the Conference on Yugoslavia
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: comply fully with their obligations in this regard [international humanitarian law and human rights in the former Yugoslavia]
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZE FRN GMY ITA RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: comply immediately with the agreement of 5 June 1992 (S/24075 annex) and ensure unimpeded access by land to Sarajevo
4.1.1_res_intro: CZR FRN GMY HON NTH OMA UKG

1.5_substance: grant unimpeded and continuous access to all camps prisons and detention centers to the International Committee of the Red Cross and other relevant humanitarian organizations and treat all detainees therein humanely including providing adequate food shelter and medical care
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: show restraint

withdraw forces and their weapons to a distance from the safe area of Gorazde (as defined in S/RES/824) at a distance to be agreed by UNPROFOR wherefrom they cease to constitute a threat to the status of Gorazde as a safe area
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG

1.5_substance: calls upon all parties to do all in their power to faciliate such access [for relevant humanitarian organizations in particular the ICRC to be granted immediate unimpeded and continued access to camps prisons and detention centers within the territory of the former Yugoslavia]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: respect fully the rights of all such persons ensure their safety and release them immediately
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZE FRN GMY ITA RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: cooperate fully with UNPROFOR and international humanitarian agencies to facilitate the evacuation by air of cases of special humanitarian concern
cooperate fully with UNPROFOR in the reopening of the airport exercise the utmost restraint and not seek any military advantage from the situation

resolve differences with opposing sides through a negotiated political solution to the problems in the region and to that end cooperate with the renewed efforts of the European Community and its member states with the support of states participating in the Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe within the framework of the Conference on Yugoslavia and in particular respond positively to the invitation of the Chairman of the Conference to talks on 15 July 1992
immediately cease armed attacks against Srebrenica and withdraw immediately from the areas surrounding Srebrenica
respect fully the safety of UNPROFOR personnel and ensure their complete freedom of movement including resupply
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN GMY ITA UKG USA

1.5_substance: take the important first step of recognizing the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina within its internationally recognized borders
4.1.1_res_intro: CZR FRN GMY UKG USA

1.5_substance: treat Srebrenica and its surroundings as a safe area which should be free from any armed attack or any other hostile act
resume forthwith negotiations towards an overall peaceful settlement on the basis of the acceptance of the Contact Group peace plan as a starting point
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN

1.5_substance: cooperate with UNPROFOR in the consolidation of the cease-fire in and around Sarajevo
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: resume discussions on constitutional arrangements for Bosnia and Herzegovina
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: accept the Contact Group peace plan as a starting point
4.1.1_res_intro: CZR FRN GMY HON NTH OMA UKG

1.5_substance: achieve with the help of the UN complete freedom of movement for the civilian population and humanitarian goods to from and within Sarajevo to remove any hindrance to such freedom of movement and help restore normal life to the city
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: fully comply with the demands set out in the Statement of its President of 18 September 1995 [cease the military offensive]
fully respect the safety of United Nations personnel
fully ensure their [UN peace forces] safety and cooperate fully with them
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZE FRN GMY ITA RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: consider the draft outline constitution as a basis for negotiating a political settlement of the conflict in [Bosnia and Herzegovina] and continue negotiations for consitutional arrangements on the basis of the draft outline under the auspices of the Co-Chairmen of the Steering Committee these negotiations to be held in continuous and uninterrupted session
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: cooperate fully and promptly with UNPROFOR towards monitoring the humanitarian situation in the Srebrenica safe area

reaffirms further the obligation of all parties to ensure the complete freedom of movement of personnel of the UN and other relevant inernational organizations throughout the territory of Bosnia and Herzegovina at all times
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZE FRN GMY ITA RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: provide suitable radio broadcasting frequencies and television broadcasting slots at no cost to the UN for the purposes described in paragraphs 47 to 51 of the SG Report of 22 March 1995 (S/1995/222 and Corr. 1) [public information campaign on behalf of UNPROFOR]
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR FRN GMY ITA RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: henceforth direct all request for authorizations of flights pursuant to paragraph 3 of S/RES/781 to UNPROFOR with special provisions being made for flights of UNPROFOR and all other flights in support of UN operations including humanitarian assistance
release infrastructure equipment and material urgently needed for humanitarian relief
comply with the cease-fire agreement signed on 29 March 1994 (S/1994/367 annex)
refrain from violence and hostile acts to reach immediately a cease-fire and a cessation of hostilities throughout the territory of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina

cooperate fully with the ICFY Mission in particular in investigating alleged breaches of the closure of the border whether by land or by air between the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) and the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina and ensuring the continued closure of that border
4.1.1_res_intro: CZR FRN GMY ITA UKG USA

1.5_substance: negotiate in good faith on the basis of the Geneva Declaration of Principles of 8 September 1995 with the aim of achieving lasting peace throughout the region

comply with commitment to cooperate fully in the investigation into the reports of helicopter flights crossing the border between the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina
4.1.1_res_intro: CZR FRN GMY ITA UKG USA

1.5_substance: decides that all States shall cooperate fully with the International Tribunal and its organs in accordance with the present resolution and the Statute of the International Tribunal and that consequently all States shall take any measures necessary under their domestic law to implement the provisions of the present resolution and the Statute including the obligation of States to comply with requests for assistance or orders issued by a Trial Chamber under Article 29 of the Statute
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN NEW RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: provide humanitarian assistance material and financial taking into accoutn the large number of refugees and displaced persons
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN UKG

1.5_substance: prevent the import of all commodities and products originating in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) exported therefrom after the date of the present resolution [30 May 1992]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: make available to the authorities in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia or to any commercial industrial or public utility undertaking in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) no funds or any other financial or economic resources within their territories and prevent their nationals and any persons within their territories from removing from their territories or otherwise making available to those authorities or to any such undertaking any such funds or resources and from remitting any other funds to persons or bodies within the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) except payments exclusively for strictly medical or humanitarian purposes and foodstuffs
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: deny permission to any aircraft to take off from land in or overfly their territory if it is destined to land in or has taken off from the territory of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) unless the particular flight has been approved for humanitarian or other purposes consistent with the relevant resolutions of the Council by the Security Council Committee established by S/RES/724 (1991)
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: prohibit by their nationals or from their territory the provision of engineering and maintenance servicing of aircraft registered in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) or operated by or on behalf of entities in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) or components for such aircraft the certification of airworthiness for such aircraft and the payment of new claims against existing insurance contracts and the provision of new direct insurance for such aircraft
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: reduce the level of the staff at diplomatic missions and consular posts of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro)
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: take the necessary steps to prevent the participation in sporting events on their territory of persons or groups representing the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro)
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: suspend scientific and technical cooperation and cultural exchanges and visits involving persons or groups officially sponsored by or representing the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro)
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: ensure that no claim shall lie at the instance of the authorities in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) or of any person or body in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) or of any person claiming through or for the benefit of any such person or body in connection with any contract or other transaction where its performance was affected by reason of the measures imposed by the present resolution and related resolutions
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: act strictly in accordance with the provisions of the present resolution [S/RES/757] notwithstanding the existence of any rights or obligations conferred or imposed by any international agreement or any contract entered into or any license or permit granted prior to the date of the present resolution [30 May 1992]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: report to the Secretary-General by 22 June 1992 on the measures they have instituted for meeting the obligations set out in paragraphs 4 to 9 in the present resolution [S/RES/757]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: cooperate fully with the Security Council Committee established by S/RES 724 (1991) in the fulfilment of its tasks including supplying such information as may be sought by the Committee in pursuance of the present resolution [S/RES/757]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: respond to the Revised Joint Appeal for humanitarian assistance of early May 1992 issued by UNHCR UNICEF and the WHO
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN HUN MOR UKG USA

1.5_substance: contribute to the international humanitarian efforts in Sarajevo and its environs
report to the Secretary-General on measures one's national government is taking in coordination with the United Nations to carry out the current resolution [S/RES/770]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: provide appropriate support for the actions undertaken in pursuance of this resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: collate substantiated information in their possession or submitted to them relating to the violations of humanitarian law including grave breaches of the Geneva Conventions being committed in the territory of the former Yugoslavia and make this information available to the Council
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: provide the Secretary-General nationally or through regional agencies or arrangements with such financial or other assistance as he deems appropriate to assist in the performance of the functions outlined in his report [S/24540-- expanding UNPROFOR]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: reaffirms its call in paragraph 5 of resolution 771 upon States and as appropriate international humanitarian organizations to collate substantiated information in their possession or submitted to them relating to the violations of humanitarian law including grave breaches of the Geneva Conventions being committed in the territory of the former Yugoslavia
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN MOR UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: make this information available within thirty days of the adoption of the present resolution and as appropriate thereafter and provide other appropriate assistance to the Commission of Experts referred to in paragraph 2 below
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN MOR UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: take nationally or through regional agencies or arrangements all measures necessary to provide assistance to UNPROFOR based on technical and monitoring capabilities for the purpose of paragraph 2 above [monitor compliance with ban on military flights including the placement of observers where necessary at airfields in the territory of the former Yugoslavia]
4.1.1_res_intro: AUS BEL FRN MOR RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: take all necessary steps to ensure that no exports from their country are diverted to the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) in violation of S/RES/757 [general economic sanctions]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: use such measures commensurate with the specific circumstances as may be necessary acting nationally or through regional agencies or arrangements under the authority of the Security Council to halt all inward and outward maritime shipping in order to inspect and verify their cargoes and destinations and ensure strict implementation of the provisions of S/RES/713 [arms embargo] and S/RES/757 [general economic sanctions]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: take necessary measures to ensure that shipping on the Danube is in accordance with S/RES/713 [arms embargo on territory of former Yugoslavia] and S/RES/757 [economic sanctions on Federal Republic of Yugoslavia] including such measures commensurate with the specific circumstances as may be necessary to halt such shipping in order to inspect and verify their cargoes and destinations and to ensure strict implementation of the provisions of S/RES/713 [arms embargo on territory of former Yugoslavia] and S/RES/757 [economic sanctions on Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: coordinate with the Secretary-General nationally or through regional agencies or arrangements on the submission of reports to the Security Council regarding actions taken in pursuance of paragraphs 12 and 13 of present resolution [on the maritime implementation of the Yugoslav embargo] to facilitate the monitoring of the implementation of the present resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: provide in accordance with the Charter of the UN such assistance as may be required by those states acting nationally or through regional agencies and arrangements in pursuance of paragraphs 12 and 13 of the present resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: contribute to the humanitarian relief efforts in the former Yugoslavia support the UN Consolidated Inter-Agency Programme of Action and Appeal for the former Yugoslavia and speed up the delivery of assistance under existing pledges
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN RUS UKG USA

1.5_substance: inform the Secretary-General of the work of its delegation [to investigate the facts received until now] (see preamb. 4)
4.1.1_res_intro: BEL FRN MOR UKG

1.5_substance: coordinate closely with the Secretary-General and UNPROFOR on the measures taken to implement [op. 4 of current resolution] including the rules of engagement and on the starting date of its implementation which should be no later than seven days from when the authority conferred in op. 4 takes effect and to report the starting date to the Council through the Secretary-General
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: inform the Secretary-General immediately of any actions taken in exercise of the authority conferred in op. 4 of the current resolution [take all necessary measures in BiH airspace to ensure compliance with the ban on flights in S/RES/781]
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: cooperate effectively with the Secretary-General acting nationally or through regional organizations or arrangements in his efforts to assist the parties in implementing the peace plan in accordance with op. 8 of current resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: in implementing the measures imposed by resolutions 757 760 787 and the present resolution take steps to prevent diversion to the territory of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) of commodities and products said to be destined for other places in particular the UN Protected Areas in the Republic of Croatia and those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: ensure that adequate monitoring is provided to all cabotage traffic involving points that are situated between Vidin/Calafat and Mohacs
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: take necessary measures to ensure that shipping on the Danube is in accordance with S/RES/713 [arms embargo on territory of former Yugoslavia] S/RES/757 [economic sanctions on Federal Republic of Yugoslavia] S/RES/787 [earlier riparian and shipping restrictions] and the present resolution including any measures under the authority of the Security Council to halt or otherwise control all shipping in order to inspect and verify their cargoes and destinations to ensure effective monitoring and to ensure strict implementation of the relevant resolutions
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: provide acting nationally or through regional organizations or arrangements such assistance as may be required by the riparian states notwithstanding the restrictions on navigation set out in the international agreements which apply to the Danube
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: bring proceedings against persons and entities violating the measures imposed by resolutions 713 757 787 and the present resolution and impose appropriate penalties
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: work in close cooperation with the Committee established by S/RES/724
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: require that all persons and entities within their own territory holding funds including any funds derived from property (a) of the authorities in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) or (b) of commercial industrial or public utility undertakings in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) or (c) controlled directly or indirectly to or for the benefit of the authorities in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) or to any commercial industrial or public utility undertaking in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) have these assets frozen in order to ensure they are not made directly or indirectly available for the benefit of the authorities in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: report to the Committee established by S/RES/724 on actions taken pursuant to op. 21 of the current resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: impound all vessels freight vehicles rolling stock and aircraft in their territories in which a majority or controlling interest is held by a person or undertaking in or operating from the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro) and that these vessels freight vehicles rolling stock and aircraft may be forfeit to the seizing state upon a determination that they have been in violation of resolutions 713 757 787 or the present resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: detain pending investigation all vessels freight vehicles rolling stock aircraft and cargoes found in their territories and suspected of having violated or being in violation of resolutions 713 757 787 or the present resolution and that upon a determination that they have been in violation such vessels freight vehicles rolling stock and aircraft shall be impounded and where appropriate they and their cargoes may be forfeit to the detaining state
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: consider what contribution they can make to the reconstruction of Bosnia and Herzegovina
4.1.1_res_intro: CAP DJI FRN MOR PAK SPN UKG USA VEN

1.5_substance: contribute funds equipment and services to the International Tribunal including the offer of expert personnel
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN NEW RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: contribute forces including logistic support to facilitate the implementation of provisions regarding the safe areas
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: coordinate closely with the Secretary-General and UNPROFOR on the measures taken to implement [op. 10 of current resolution] and report to the Council through the Secretary-General
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: coordinate closely acting nationally or through regional organizations or arrangements with the Secretary-General in the use of air power in and around the safe areas to support UNPROFOR in the performance of its mandate [as detailed in op. 10 of S/RES/836]
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: contribute forces including logistic support and equipment to facilitate the implementation of the provisions regarding the safe areas
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: contribute to a voluntary trust fund [to be established by the Secretary-General] whose assets will be disbursed within the framework set out in [op. 3 of current resolution] for the restoration of essential public services in Sarajevo to promote a return to normal life in the city
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: assist the Secretary-General in particular by contributing personnel and equipment in the implementation of relevant Security Council resolutions concerning Bosnia and Herzegovina
4.1.1_res_intro: FRN RUS SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: assist the Secretary-General to implement op. 4 and 5 of current resolution [increase in UNPROFOR size and capability] by contributing personnel equipment and training

make voluntary financial contributions to the trust fund [established by the Secretary-General for the restoration of essential public services in and around Sarajevo in accordance with the provisions of S/RES/900]
continue efforts to restore normal life to all areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina
cooperate in an effective manner acting nationally or through regional agencies or arrangements with the Secretary-General in his efforts to aid the parties to implement the proposed settlement
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: desist from any political talks with the leadership of the Bosnian Serb party as long as that party has not accepted the proposed settlement in full
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: prevent economic activities carried on after the date of adoption of this resolution within their territories by any entity wherever incorporated or constituted which is owned or controlled directly or indirectly by (a) any person in or resident in or any entity including any commercial industrial or public utility undertaking in those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces or (b) any entity incorporated in or constituted under the law of those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: prevent economic activities carried on after the date of adoption of this resolution within their territories by any entity including those identified by states for the purpose of this resolution found to be acting for or on behalf of and to the benefit of any entity including any commercial industrial or public utility undertaking in those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces or any entity identified in subparagraph (i) above
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: revoke existing and issue no further authorization under paragraph 7 (of the current resolution) in respect of any person or entity violating the measures imposed by this resolution or violating the measures imposed by earlier relevant resolutions where those violations have occurred after the date of adoption of this resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: require all persons and entities within their territories holding funds or other financial assets or resources of (i) any entity including any commercial industrial or public utility undertaking in those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces or (ii) any entity identified in paragraph 7 (i) of the current resolution or any person or entity identified in paragraph 7 (ii) of the current resolution to freeze them to ensure that neither they nor any other funds or any other financial assets or resources are made available directly or indirectly to or for the benefit of any of the above-mentioned persons or entities except (a) payments made in connection with activities authorized in accordance with paragraph 7 of the current resolution or payments made in connection with transactions authorized by the Government of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina with regard to persons or entities within its territory provided that states are satisfied that payments to persons outside their territories will be used for the purpose or in connection with the activities and transactions for which permission is sought; and that in the case of payments made under exception (a) above states may authorize such payments only after they are satisfied on a case-by-case basis that the payments do not result in the transfer of funds or other financial assets or resources to any person or entity described in subparagraph (a) or (b) of paragraph 7(i) of the current resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: ensure that all payments of dividends interest or other income on shares interest bonds or debt obligations or amounts derived from an interest in or the sale or other disposal of or any other dealing with tangible and intangible assets and property rights accruing to (i) any entity including any commercial industrial or public utility undertaking in those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of the Bosnian Serb forces or (ii) any entity identified in paragraph 7(ii) of the current resolution are made only into frozen accounts
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: prevent the entry into their territory of the members of the authorities including legislative authorities in those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces and officers of the Bosnian Serb military and paramilitary forces and those acting on behalf of such authorities or forces
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: prevent the entry into their territory of persons found after the adoption of the present resolution to have provided financial material logistical military or any tangible support to Bosnian Serb forces in violation of relevant resolutions of the Council
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: prevent the entry into their territory of persons in or resident in those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces found to have violated or contributed to the violation of the measures set out in S/RES/820 and in the present resolution
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: prohibit all commercial riverine traffic from entering ports of those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces except when authorized on a case-by-case basis by the Committee established by resolution 724 or by the Government of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina for its territory or in case of force majeure
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: require that all shipments of commodities and products destined for those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces be properly manifested and either be physically inspected by the Sanctions Assistance Missions or the competent national authorities at loading to verify and seal their contents or be laden in such a manner which permits adequate physical verification of the contents
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: in implementing the measures imposed by this resolution to prevent take steps to prevent the diversion of benefits to those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of the Bosnian Serb forces from other places and in particular from the UN Protected areas in Croatia
4.1.1_res_intro: ARG CZR DJI FRN GMY NIG OMA PAK RUS RWA SPN UKG USA

1.5_substance: in implementing the measures imposed by this resolution take steps to prevent the diversion of benefits to those areas of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina under the control of Bosnian Serb forces from other places and in particular from the United Nations Protected Areas in Croatia
